File: Comair's business rescue practitioners have asked creditors for a short extension for the publication of its business rescue plan. JOHANNESBURG - Comair is extending the grounding of Kulula and British Airways flights until the end of August. This follows President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement that the country will remain on an adjusted level 4 lockdown. READ: Comair to halve its fleet This prolongs the ban on non-essential travel into and out of Gauteng. People with tickets for travel between 28 June and 31 August will be able to reschedule flights and use their tickets within twelve months after August. Comair is still under business rescue, after massive losses accumulated last year.